President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in Nebraska due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred on December 15, 2021. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available to governments and nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repairs, and replacements on a cost-sharing basis. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. DuWayne Tewes has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.